  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

  <p>Effective date: <strong>2025-10-11</strong></p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy applies to the app <strong>Ghost Words</strong> and explains how the developer <strong>Ghost DEV</strong> handles user information.</p>

  <h3>1. Information Collected</h3>
  <p>The app stores text entered by the user locally on the device. No account registration is required. We do not automatically collect personal information such as name, email address, or device identifiers.</p>

  <h3>2. How We Use Data</h3>
  <p>Data stored locally is used only to provide the app's learning and display features. We do not transmit or share user data with external servers or third parties unless explicitly stated.</p>

  <h3>3. Third-Party Sharing</h3>
  <p>We do not share user personal information with third parties.</p>

  <h3>4. Security</h3>
  <p>Data is stored only on the user's device. We take reasonable measures to protect data, but device security remains the user's responsibility.</p>

  <h3>5. User Rights</h3>
  <p>Users can edit or delete saved texts directly within the app. For additional support, contact the address below.</p>

  <h3>6. Contact</h3>
  <p>Email: <a href="mailto:gho2t.dev@gmail.com">gho2t.dev@gmail.com</a></p>

